stanford pan asian music festival elegant gathering iii events at stanford stanford pan asian music festival elegant gathering iii facebook twitter email print add to calendar lectures and demonstrations associated with the eighth annual pan asian music festival take the format of elegant gatherings an ancient term used to describe a gathering of scholars and artists anna schultz ethnomusicology professor in the department of music moderates a panel discussion with the theme from the silk road to today's world of music that will explore the past and the continuing transformation of asian music followed by a chinese tea ceremony performed by tea master chiung chih lin presented in collaboration with the center for east asian studies at stanford when saturday february 11 2012 1 00 pm where dinkelspiel auditorium map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags arts performance music sponsor department of music admission free permalink http events stanford edu events 305 30549 last modified january 26 2012
